LORE verdant-guide
FLAGS WILDERNESS KIESS
Forest of Confusion: failed druidic quarantine merged with Verdant Depths'
distributed intelligence; the mist is not natural weather
Mist-fever: psychoactive disorientation; false memories, inability to
determine direction, temporal confusion; prolonged exposure causes permanent
cognitive effects; onset can be sudden
Kiess Wall Command rope-line corridors through the southern verge: attach
to the rope before entering; do not leave the rope without a guide
Verdant Depths at the forest core: living intelligence with growth/decay/
predation aspects; Heartwood Guardians protect the core; no city contact
Withered Depths: Conclave crystal blight in root systems; plant-based
creatures are aggressive; contact with corrupted organic matter propagates
blight; treat as contamination, not combat
Salvage routes (herbs, rare timber, relic fragments) are profitable; get
in, get it, and get out; people who linger don't always return as themselves
~
